<dl id="n54146a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54146a">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54146a"> 146(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> all churinga = 1 body <small>Green</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n54146a"><li>FW 25.16ff </li><li><a href="../../flex/a/lexa.htm#n54146a">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/a/l39a.htm#n54146a">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n54146a">MS BL 47476b-474</ms> </li><li>JJA 50:278 <a name="ad8" href="../../FF/fdra/ada.htm#ad8">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/a/ad8.htm#n54146a">Draft: I.1&sect;1.8</a>/2.8</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">&laquo;Le corps (de l&apos;anc&ecirc;tre mythique) resta &agrave; un certain endroit, o&ugrave; furent fabriqu&eacute;s plusieurs churinga de bois, dont le pouvoir provenait du corps qui demeura l&agrave;. Ces churinga de bois &mdash; au nombre de quatre, je crois, -forment un seul corps, et deux <mark>churinga</mark> de pierre, joints aux premiers, ne <mark>forment encore avec eux qu&apos;un seul corps</mark>. Par suite, le vieillard, mort r&eacute;cemment &agrave; Alice Springs, et qui &eacute;tait la r&eacute;incarnation de cet anc&ecirc;tre mythique, regardait les deux churinga de pierre comme son propre corps, qui avait continu&eacute; de vivre au cours des si&egrave;cles; mais il regardait aussi les churinga de bois comme faisant partie de son corps surnaturel et imp&eacute;rissable.&raquo; <br><font color="green">[The body (of the mythical ancestor) remained in a certain place, where several wooden churinga were made, whose power came from the body which remained there. These wooden churinga&mdash;four in number, I believe&mdash;form a single body, and two stone churinga, joined to the first, still form with them only one body. As a result, the old man, who died recently in Alice Springs, and who was the reincarnation of this mythical ancestor, regarded the two stone churingas as his own body, which had continued to live over the centuries; but he also regarded the wooden churinga as part of his supernatural and imperishable body.]</font> <small> Lucian L&eacute;vy-Bruhl, <a name="LBEM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#LBEM"><cite title="source">L'exp&eacute;rience mystique</cite></a> (1938) 202</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
